(I actually sold the rat whiskers for the grand sum of one gold, three silver!)<br>
<br>
I've asked a few other folks and it seems there's somewhat of a consensus we should let guildmembers have, or at least use, the stuff Zulu gave us.<br>
<br>
Grimmbaldis in particular brought up a great point -- by the time people have leveled up to where they can really use that kind of stuff, they can get it themselves!<br>
<br>
I agree with that.  Our guild is founded on kindness, but there's no reason we can't be kind to each other, too!  In any case, Zulu did say the items were for the guild, and I can see his point.  We spend a lot of time helping others, while other guilds spend their time getting items for members.<br>
<br>
Grimmy says he can use the Polished Granite Tomahawk, so I'll be glad to take it to him in Kunark (it turns out the PGT is worth less than I thought. I had it mixed up with something completely different, a Short Sword of Ykesha.  No, I don't know how I made that assumption).  Kizor, let me know next time we are both on and I can meet you someplace to give you the Obsidian Ring.<br>
<br>
That leaves a Trueshot Longbow and a Sarnak Emblazoned Tabard.  If no one can use those things, I'll be glad to either give them to Ealwen for the treasury, or auction them at the East Commons Bazaar -- we could then use the money to buy lower-end items for guildmembers or to use as prizes for future events.<br>
<br>
I hope this is okay with everybody.  I ended up with these items not because I'm trying to take over the job of treasurer (Please, Cruise Director is quite enough!), but because they were ostensibly going to be prizes in my giveaway on Thursday.<br>
<br>
Fortunately, Tchallar gave me some nice stuff for Thursday, so we're all set.  Pikaa, if you are reading this, I am also giving away the Runed Totem Staff you got for me in Paw (miss you!!!).  Qandar, the guy I was originally going to give the staff to, ended up getting another one from a friend.<br>
<br>
If anyone has objections, please, make them known.  I want whatever we end up doing to be agreeable to most of us.<br>
<br>
Thanks for reading,<br>
<br>
